WEBVTT FILE

1
00:00:05.840 --> 00:00:08.915
♪

2
00:00:09.068 --> 00:00:10.567
(dog barking in distance)

3
00:00:10.586 --> 00:00:20.519
♪

4
00:00:32.867 --> 00:00:34.450
(woman giggling)

5
00:00:36.929 --> 00:00:38.620
(sensuous giggling)

6
00:00:39.856 --> 00:00:41.165
Group:
Surprise!

7
00:00:48.883 --> 00:00:49.840
Roger?

8
00:00:51.277 --> 00:00:53.460
Ashley, what are you doing home?

9
00:00:53.612 --> 00:00:55.779
What am I doing...?

10
00:00:55.798 --> 00:00:57.473
I'm throwing my husband a
birthday party.

11
00:01:11.964 --> 00:01:12.905
Wow.

12
00:01:17.152 --> 00:01:23.490
♪

13
00:01:23.584 --> 00:01:24.708
Ash...

14
00:01:34.077 --> 00:01:35.819
Wait, ashley...
Ashley, wait!

15
00:01:35.912 --> 00:01:37.096
Five years, ash. Five years.

16
00:01:37.323 --> 00:01:39.489
You can't just end it
over some fling.

17
00:01:39.508 --> 00:01:40.991
It just did.

18
00:01:41.009 --> 00:01:42.434
Happy birthday.

19
00:01:48.943 --> 00:01:49.858
(hitting table)

20
00:01:54.857 --> 00:01:59.767
♪

21
00:01:59.787 --> 00:02:01.769
(ship's horn sounding)

22
00:02:01.864 --> 00:02:07.609
♪

23
00:02:07.628 --> 00:02:10.036
I just got
the most interesting call.

24
00:02:10.189 --> 00:02:11.538
Oh?

25
00:02:11.690 --> 00:02:14.207
From none other than
mrs. Jacqueline james.

26
00:02:14.360 --> 00:02:16.543
(gasping)
the restaurateur?

27
00:02:16.695 --> 00:02:18.470
Yes! She wants to meet.

28
00:02:18.697 --> 00:02:20.213
She's renovating an old
location,

29
00:02:20.366 --> 00:02:21.974
And she's interested in
one of my murals.

30
00:02:22.201 --> 00:02:23.809
Ah! She saw the work you did
at bodega's?

31
00:02:24.036 --> 00:02:25.126
I guess so!

32
00:02:25.146 --> 00:02:27.295
-Aw, that's amazing!
-Right?

33
00:02:27.314 --> 00:02:29.539
Ashley, it's so nice to hear you
get some good news.

34
00:02:29.558 --> 00:02:31.541
I know.

35
00:02:31.635 --> 00:02:33.543
Tess: You know, I can't believe
it's been a year

36
00:02:33.637 --> 00:02:35.228
Since you and roger split.

37
00:02:35.381 --> 00:02:36.730
Since I left him, you mean.

38
00:02:36.824 --> 00:02:39.883
Yes. One whole year since you
were brutally robbed

39
00:02:39.902 --> 00:02:42.235
Of the ability to trust another
human being.

40
00:02:42.388 --> 00:02:43.996
Eh, I wouldn't go that far.

41
00:02:44.147 --> 00:02:45.831
- I mean, I trust you.
- Yeah.

42
00:02:45.982 --> 00:02:48.834
I trust my dad.
I trust the weather guy on tv.

43
00:02:48.985 --> 00:02:50.911
Oh, no, don't trust
the weather guy.

44
00:02:51.063 --> 00:02:52.913
-No, he lies.
-(chuckling)

45
00:02:53.065 --> 00:02:55.323
I do think you should start
dating again, though, you know,

46
00:02:55.342 --> 00:02:57.342
- Just for practice.
- Uh-uh.

47
00:02:58.995 --> 00:03:01.571
So, I'm on this
new dating app, and...

48
00:03:01.590 --> 00:03:03.073
Pass. I'm good.

49
00:03:03.091 --> 00:03:06.760
Look, they're a lot better than
they used to be, I swear.

50
00:03:06.854 --> 00:03:08.687
What's your kickback?

51
00:03:08.914 --> 00:03:12.249
10% off my subscription for
every new referral.

52
00:03:12.267 --> 00:03:13.934
Hmm. Okay.

53
00:03:14.086 --> 00:03:17.845
And you, um, you may have
already signed up.

54
00:03:17.865 --> 00:03:20.348
What?! Tess! What did you do?

55
00:03:20.442 --> 00:03:22.868
I just-- I took some of your
pictures and I plugged them in,

56
00:03:23.019 --> 00:03:24.703
And then... Voila!

57
00:03:24.930 --> 00:03:25.946
Voila what?

58
00:03:26.098 --> 00:03:28.022
Don't tell me I've already
gotten messages.

59
00:03:28.042 --> 00:03:30.434
Obviously, yeah.
You're breathtaking.

60
00:03:30.452 --> 00:03:32.602
Wait, what photo did you use?
Let me see that.

61
00:03:32.621 --> 00:03:33.787
It's cute.

62
00:03:33.881 --> 00:03:36.215
Oh my-- tess!

63
00:03:36.366 --> 00:03:39.109
No. Okay, you know what?
I don't want to see it.

64
00:03:39.127 --> 00:03:42.054
Just purge the account
in some digital fire.

65
00:03:42.281 --> 00:03:43.613
I'm not interested.

66
00:03:43.707 --> 00:03:45.298
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

67
00:03:45.451 --> 00:03:48.118
We have both put a lot of work
into this.

68
00:03:48.136 --> 00:03:49.728
Have you been replying
on my behalf?

69
00:03:49.879 --> 00:03:52.213
No, no! I would never.

70
00:03:52.307 --> 00:03:55.067
I just, you know, provided
a door for others to knock on.

71
00:03:55.218 --> 00:03:58.737
It is up to you if you want
to answer.

72
00:04:00.132 --> 00:04:01.815
Yeah, no.

73
00:04:01.909 --> 00:04:03.633
I don't know.

74
00:04:03.652 --> 00:04:04.743
No, no.

75
00:04:06.080 --> 00:04:07.412
Fine.

76
00:04:11.477 --> 00:04:14.978
(music plays softly)

77
00:04:14.997 --> 00:04:17.831
♪

78
00:04:17.983 --> 00:04:20.166
♪ I... ♪

79
00:04:20.261 --> 00:04:23.077
(sighing)

80
00:04:23.097 --> 00:04:24.429
Fine.

81
00:04:27.101 --> 00:04:29.768
"spiritual vegan." okay.

82
00:04:32.273 --> 00:04:35.274
"I'm an open book,
ask me anything."

83
00:04:35.425 --> 00:04:37.067
Sure you are, buddy.

84
00:04:39.354 --> 00:04:40.612
Hmm.

85
00:04:42.116 --> 00:04:43.699
Hello, marco.

86
00:04:47.288 --> 00:04:48.770
(app chiming)

87
00:04:48.789 --> 00:04:53.274
♪

88
00:04:53.368 --> 00:04:55.043
(phone chiming)

89
00:04:58.857 --> 00:05:00.114
What?!

90
00:05:00.208 --> 00:05:05.879
♪

91
00:05:05.973 --> 00:05:09.474
♪ come together... ♪

92
00:05:11.553 --> 00:05:13.961
Jacqueline: It is so nice
to meet you, ashley.

93
00:05:14.056 --> 00:05:15.221
I'm jacqueline.

94
00:05:15.374 --> 00:05:17.316
Don't mind the dust,
the kitchen's been closed

95
00:05:17.543 --> 00:05:19.876
- For the renovations.
- Wow, what a space,

96
00:05:19.895 --> 00:05:21.302
Yeah, my pride and joy.

97
00:05:21.322 --> 00:05:23.805
Passed down for three
generations.

98
00:05:23.824 --> 00:05:25.382
But, like everything in life,

99
00:05:25.400 --> 00:05:27.809
We must adapt to the times
or be left behind.

100
00:05:27.828 --> 00:05:29.736
Which is why I rely on the
talent of youth

101
00:05:29.830 --> 00:05:31.830
When we're redecorating.

102
00:05:31.981 --> 00:05:35.149
Now, I am picturing one of your
mixed media pieces here.

103
00:05:35.243 --> 00:05:37.318
- Filling the pace.
- Okay.

104
00:05:37.338 --> 00:05:39.729
I am having some electrical
upgrades done

105
00:05:39.823 --> 00:05:41.322
While you complete the mural,

106
00:05:41.342 --> 00:05:44.084
If you can meet the deadline,
that is.

107
00:05:44.236 --> 00:05:46.762
I am scheduled to reopen the
first of the month.

108
00:05:48.090 --> 00:05:50.256
First of the month. Um...

109
00:05:50.409 --> 00:05:53.185
Tight, but yes, I can do it.

110
00:05:53.412 --> 00:05:55.745
Wonderful.
How soon can you start?

111
00:05:55.839 --> 00:05:58.081
Uh, actually I'd love to get
started right away

112
00:05:58.174 --> 00:05:59.841
- If possible.
- Fantastic.

113
00:05:59.860 --> 00:06:01.008
- Grant?
- Mm-hm?

114
00:06:01.028 --> 00:06:02.343
This is ashley morris.

115
00:06:02.437 --> 00:06:03.845
She's gonna be working here
with you.

116
00:06:03.864 --> 00:06:05.030
- Hi.
- Hey.

117
00:06:05.181 --> 00:06:08.200
Here is a key,
you can just let yourself out.

118
00:06:08.351 --> 00:06:09.851
And, uh...

119
00:06:09.945 --> 00:06:13.096
I can't tell you how excited I
am to see the finished product.

120
00:06:13.189 --> 00:06:14.831
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

121
00:06:18.604 --> 00:06:20.862
Grant:
I can never find my tools.

122
00:06:20.956 --> 00:06:23.123
(rattling)
crazy.

123
00:06:23.275 --> 00:06:24.774
- Oh.
- (cell phone chiming)

124
00:06:24.793 --> 00:06:26.776
Grant: I pack my own back and I
can even find my own tools.

125
00:06:26.870 --> 00:06:28.053
Excuse me.

126
00:06:31.541 --> 00:06:34.300
(giggling)

127
00:06:34.453 --> 00:06:35.969
Is it a wrong number?

128
00:06:36.063 --> 00:06:38.146
No. Sorry.

129
00:06:39.975 --> 00:06:43.217
My friend signed me up on this
new matchmaking site,

130
00:06:43.237 --> 00:06:45.404
So now I get a...

131
00:06:45.631 --> 00:06:48.222
Little dopamine jolt every time
my phone dings.

132
00:06:48.316 --> 00:06:50.300
- Sounds exhausting.
- Yeah.

133
00:06:50.393 --> 00:06:52.152
- And horribly addicting.
- Yeah.

134
00:06:52.304 --> 00:06:54.746
It's a waste of time anyway.

135
00:06:54.898 --> 00:06:56.473
Romance is my curse.

136
00:06:56.566 --> 00:06:58.917
Okay, okay, now you just sound
like a defeatist.

137
00:06:59.144 --> 00:07:00.252
(chuckling)

138
00:07:03.406 --> 00:07:05.665
I have a feeling that things are
gonna turn around for you soon.

139
00:07:05.759 --> 00:07:07.008
Thank you.

140
00:07:11.990 --> 00:07:19.420
♪

141
00:07:19.514 --> 00:07:20.897
(clearing throat)

142
00:07:23.351 --> 00:07:25.259
Ashley, hey. You there?

143
00:07:25.279 --> 00:07:27.112
- Marco?
- Ashley?

144
00:07:27.263 --> 00:07:29.281
Can you hear me? I think we have
a bad connection.

145
00:07:31.118 --> 00:07:33.026
- Oh.
- Okay.

146
00:07:33.178 --> 00:07:35.102
Hey. I think-- yep!

147
00:07:35.197 --> 00:07:38.014
- There you are.
- Hi.

148
00:07:38.107 --> 00:07:39.791
Marco:
And you look beautiful.

149
00:07:40.018 --> 00:07:41.793
Wow.

150
00:07:42.020 --> 00:07:43.962
Your pictures do not
do you justice.

151
00:07:44.189 --> 00:07:46.298
Thank you. You too.

152
00:07:46.449 --> 00:07:50.043
I mean, you look nice.
I like your suit.

153
00:07:50.195 --> 00:07:53.546
Marco: Oh, this old thing?
No, this is a job requirement.

154
00:07:53.699 --> 00:07:56.216
It's a uniform like any other.

155
00:07:56.368 --> 00:07:58.535
Where are you right now?

156
00:07:58.553 --> 00:08:01.462
I'm just at the office,
it's-- it's boring.

157
00:08:01.556 --> 00:08:03.631
To be honest, I wish...

158
00:08:03.650 --> 00:08:06.151
I wish I did something more like
what you do for a living,

159
00:08:06.302 --> 00:08:07.819
You know, working with
your hands,

160
00:08:07.971 --> 00:08:09.637
Crafting your own designs.

161
00:08:09.731 --> 00:08:13.399
Oh, you make me sound like some
avant garde artist.

162
00:08:13.494 --> 00:08:16.903
I'm basically just a glorified
tile setter.

163
00:08:17.055 --> 00:08:19.556
Ashley, you sell yourself short.

164
00:08:19.649 --> 00:08:21.074
I've seen your portfolio,
remember?

165
00:08:21.168 --> 00:08:23.243
Your work is stunning.

166
00:08:23.337 --> 00:08:25.395
Thank you.

167
00:08:25.413 --> 00:08:26.838
You know,

168
00:08:26.990 --> 00:08:31.251
I've gotta admit, this whole
thing feels a little strange.

169
00:08:31.403 --> 00:08:35.013
I mean, dating someone I've
never actually met in person.

170
00:08:35.164 --> 00:08:37.331
Don't get me wrong, I've been
really enjoying

171
00:08:37.425 --> 00:08:39.667
Our conversations.

172
00:08:39.686 --> 00:08:44.189
But they don't quite replace
the real thing, do they?

173
00:08:44.416 --> 00:08:45.690
Yeah.

174
00:08:48.344 --> 00:08:49.986
Which is why, I, um--

175
00:08:52.849 --> 00:08:55.942
All right, I'd like you to
indulge me in something, okay?

176
00:08:56.094 --> 00:08:57.869
Okay.

177
00:08:58.021 --> 00:08:59.279
Close your eyes.

178
00:08:59.431 --> 00:09:00.789
Ashley: Okay.
(giggling)

179
00:09:05.194 --> 00:09:09.047
Marco: Now, I want you to
picture that we're at

180
00:09:09.198 --> 00:09:12.366
A charming little bistro
in paris.

181
00:09:12.386 --> 00:09:15.554
Just down the slope from
montmartre.

182
00:09:15.781 --> 00:09:17.538
There's a table right
in the back.

183
00:09:17.558 --> 00:09:19.975
- Can you see it?
- I think so.

184
00:09:22.545 --> 00:09:24.137
There's a candle flickering.

185
00:09:24.231 --> 00:09:26.956
You can feel its warmth against
your skin.

186
00:09:26.975 --> 00:09:29.292
We dimly recall having ordered,

187
00:09:29.385 --> 00:09:31.486
But we don't remember what
or when.

188
00:09:33.240 --> 00:09:35.907
The conversation is flowing,
the wine keeps coming.

189
00:09:38.153 --> 00:09:42.414
And you and I can stay there at
this little place we created

190
00:09:42.565 --> 00:09:44.040
As long as we want.

191
00:09:45.994 --> 00:09:54.926
♪

192
00:09:58.432 --> 00:10:00.348
(birds chirping)

193
00:10:18.677 --> 00:10:20.360
Tess (on phone):
And you fell asleep together?

194
00:10:20.454 --> 00:10:21.678
What are you, 16?

195
00:10:21.771 --> 00:10:24.180
Is he gonna invite you
to the sock hop next?

196
00:10:24.199 --> 00:10:26.683
No! We just lost track of time,
you know?

197
00:10:26.776 --> 00:10:28.201
He was telling me about
his childhood,

198
00:10:28.353 --> 00:10:30.295
And I told him about my mom,

199
00:10:30.522 --> 00:10:32.355
And, you know,
losing her so young.

200
00:10:32.448 --> 00:10:35.024
That was like, our fifth night
in a row.

201
00:10:35.043 --> 00:10:37.118
- It's crazy.
- Hey!

202
00:10:37.137 --> 00:10:38.637
- Oh no, roger is here.
- Tess: At the restaurant?

203
00:10:38.864 --> 00:10:40.196
I gotta go,
I'll call you back.

204
00:10:40.215 --> 00:10:42.532
Who's that guy, ashley?
Did you find a new partner?

205
00:10:42.550 --> 00:10:44.476
You didn't think I'd hear about
you poaching my commissions?

206
00:10:44.627 --> 00:10:45.793
Roger, we don't work together
anymore, remember?

207
00:10:45.812 --> 00:10:47.461
And if you were up for this job,

208
00:10:47.481 --> 00:10:48.813
I'm only finding out
about it now.

209
00:10:48.965 --> 00:10:50.540
I'm just trying to put food on
my table too, ashley.

210
00:10:50.633 --> 00:10:52.317
I didn't know you'd be
my competition.

211
00:10:52.468 --> 00:10:54.653
We're not competitors.
We do very different work.

212
00:10:54.804 --> 00:10:56.546
I'm not letting you steal
anymore gigs from me.

213
00:10:56.639 --> 00:10:57.822
- I'm warning you.
- I'm not stealing.

214
00:10:57.974 --> 00:10:59.658
- What is this?
- It's a letter from my lawyer.

215
00:10:59.809 --> 00:11:01.401
Demanding you to stop using
our company's name.

216
00:11:01.495 --> 00:11:03.828
- You agreed to this.
- I changed my mind.

217
00:11:05.390 --> 00:11:06.331
(door banging open)

218
00:11:09.485 --> 00:11:10.960
What was that about?

219
00:11:12.339 --> 00:11:13.487
Nothing.

220
00:11:13.581 --> 00:11:15.840
Just... It's fine.

221
00:11:15.992 --> 00:11:18.677
Roger and I used to own this
business together,

222
00:11:18.828 --> 00:11:21.421
And after our divorce,
we agreed I'd keep the name

223
00:11:21.573 --> 00:11:23.256
As long as I'd buy him out.

224
00:11:23.350 --> 00:11:25.666
I guess he's already running out
of patience.

225
00:11:25.686 --> 00:11:27.001
Grant:
Are you-- are you okay?

226
00:11:27.020 --> 00:11:28.669
Yeah, yeah, I'm fine.

227
00:11:28.763 --> 00:11:31.414
It just makes me so angry that
he thinks he can just

228
00:11:31.433 --> 00:11:33.841
Force his way back into my life
still, you know?

229
00:11:33.860 --> 00:11:35.860
- Anyway, let's go.
- Okay.

230
00:11:40.108 --> 00:11:50.041
♪

231
00:11:57.459 --> 00:11:59.125
Ashley:
Well, well.

232
00:11:59.219 --> 00:12:02.111
If it isn't santa claus!

233
00:12:02.205 --> 00:12:03.537
- Oh, it's arrived!
- Yes!

234
00:12:03.557 --> 00:12:06.282
- That's wonderful.
- Marco, I...

235
00:12:06.301 --> 00:12:08.727
I can't accept this,
this is too much.

236
00:12:08.954 --> 00:12:11.788
I just want you to feel
comfortable on your trip.

237
00:12:11.806 --> 00:12:13.380
You said the restaurant had to
be empty

238
00:12:13.475 --> 00:12:15.458
For the painters this weekend,
right?

239
00:12:15.551 --> 00:12:19.295
It's my chance to fly you out
here to see me.

240
00:12:19.314 --> 00:12:22.723
Honestly, after the day
I had today, I mean,

241
00:12:22.817 --> 00:12:26.152
A weekend getaway sounds
amazing.

242
00:12:26.304 --> 00:12:29.138
Oh, no, it's something with
your ex again?

243
00:12:29.157 --> 00:12:31.824
Um, roger?

244
00:12:31.977 --> 00:12:33.159
You know what,
it doesn't matter.

245
00:12:33.311 --> 00:12:35.754
Let's talk about something
more exciting.

246
00:12:35.905 --> 00:12:39.406
Like, how am I going to come
all the way from rockport,

247
00:12:39.501 --> 00:12:43.336
Massachusetts to the beautiful
island of little inagua?

248
00:12:43.488 --> 00:12:46.264
Well, ashley, that's a...
That's a good question.

249
00:12:46.415 --> 00:12:49.659
My secretary will book you
a first class fare.

250
00:12:49.677 --> 00:12:52.419
A car will come and pick you up
to take you to the airport,

251
00:12:52.514 --> 00:12:55.832
And all you need to do
is pack.

252
00:12:55.850 --> 00:12:57.517
Let me spoil you.

253
00:12:57.669 --> 00:13:00.003
Okay. Sounds great!

254
00:13:00.096 --> 00:13:01.854
(giggling)

255
00:13:02.007 --> 00:13:04.841
(cell phone ringing)

256
00:13:04.859 --> 00:13:08.269
- Is something wrong?
- (marco sighing)

